HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 926
By McKenzie
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Lonsdale Elementary School
upon its academic improvement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pay tribute to those public schools in Tennessee
that, through the natural talents and unflagging commitment to academic excellence evidenced
by their administration, faculty, staff, students, and parents, have achieved significant
milestones; and
WHEREAS, one such school is Lonsdale Elementary School in Knoxville, which recently
officially exited the priority school list after having exhibited steady progress and a commitment
to long-term growth by ensuring all students have access to strong instruction, targeted support,
and high expectations; and
WHEREAS, each year, the Tennessee Department of Education identifies schools for
additional support based on indicators such as student achievement and growth, attendance,
and English language proficiency; and
WHEREAS, schools designated as "Priority," also known as Comprehensive Support
and Improvement, remain on the list until they demonstrate sustained improvement over time;
Lonsdale's exit reflects steady progress built through intentional systems and a shared focus on
students; and
WHEREAS, Principal William Smith and the administration, faculty, and staff of Lonsdale
Elementary School have built an environment that ensures students have the very best
atmosphere for learning; and
WHEREAS, Lonsdale Elementary School's exemplary achievement is a tremendous
source of pride for the administration, teachers, students, and parents of the community; and
HJR0926
013011
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the dedication to academic excellence demonstrated by all the fine
individuals affiliated with Lonsdale Elementary School is clearly deserving of our respect,
admiration, and commendation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we congratulate Lonsdale Elementary School on exiting the priority school
list, commend the school's administration, faculty, staff, students, and parents on this
achievement, and extend to them our best wishes for continued success in the future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
